		<![CDATA[<b>Another Hacker Hits Microsoft</b>

One week after Microsoft reported that a hacker had gotten into its computer networks, another hacker said he entered the company’s web servers. The hacker, using the name Dimitri, logged on to several of Microsoft’s web servers and downloaded files containing confidential company information. A Microsoft spokesperson said, “There is always a possibility that hackers can get into a company’s network… There are bad people out there who will try to do bad things.”]]>
